For my student digital portfolio, I created and updated profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle. GitHub is mainly used for sharing and managing code, where I plan to upload my academic projects and practice coding regularly. LinkedIn is a professional networking platform that helps connect with peers, teachers, and industry professionals. I have updated my education details there and will use it to build my professional identity and explore career opportunities. Kaggle is a platform for data science and machine learning, where users can work on datasets and participate in competitions. As I am interested in learning new technical skills, I plan to use Kaggle to practice data analysis and improve my knowledge in this field.
Over the next four years, I aim to actively use these platforms to showcase my work, learn new skills, and build a strong digital presence. These platforms will help me grow academically and professionally, preparing me for future job opportunities.
